-- Irish Lenders’ ECB Borrowings Rise to 136.40 Billion Euros
-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 2010-12-10T11:17:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-10/irish-lenders-borrowing-from-european-central-bank-rise-to-180-6-billion.html
Irish-based lenders’ borrowings from
the European Central Bank rose to 136.40 billion euros ($181
billion) on Nov. 26 from 130 billion euros at the end of
October, according to statistics published on the central bank’s
website today.  The figures include international and domestic financial
institutions based in Ireland. The country’s central bank only
provides an update on the ECB funding reliance of domestic
institutions at the end of every month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Brennan in Dublin at 
